%I A395422 #10 May 02 2026 00:09:48
%S A395422 2,4,6,9,12,17,22,27,31
%N A395422 Minimum number of triangular cells in a connected polyiamond container that contains every fixed n-iamond as a translated subset.
%C A395422 A fixed n-iamond is a connected set of n unit triangles on the triangular lattice, counted up to parity-preserving translation only; rotations and reflections are distinct pieces. The count is A001420(n), with A001420(1) = 2 (up- and down-pointing unit triangles).
%C A395422 a(n) is the minimum number of cells in a connected polyiamond containing every fixed n-iamond as a translated subset.
%C A395422 Each reported value a(n) for n = 1..9 is established by SAT search inside an n X n rectangle (1 X 2 for n = 1) and then re-verified by SAT search inside the strictly larger (n+1) X (n+1) window with a drat-trim VERIFIED DRAT proof of UNSAT at size a(n) - 1 (verdict "s DERIVATION"). The wider-window certificate rules out the only structural assumption the n X n search could leave open, and renders every reported value unconditional within the (n+1) X (n+1) window. Each value is also independently cross-checked by two further verifiers with disjoint code paths from the main solver: a pure-Python geometric containment verifier and an independent SAT re-derivation that uses a different solver (Glucose 4.2).
%H A395422 Peter Exley, <a href="https://github.com/pexley-math/oeis-A395422">Solver code, verifiers, and figures</a>, GitHub.
%e A395422 For n = 1, a(1) = 2: the 2-cell rhombus formed by one up-pointing and one down-pointing unit triangle contains both fixed 1-iamonds.
%e A395422 For n = 2, a(2) = 4: contains all 3 fixed 2-iamonds.
%e A395422 For n = 3, a(3) = 6: contains all 6 fixed 3-iamonds; the 6-cell hexagon is an optimal container.
%e A395422 For n = 9, a(9) = 31: contains all 1838 fixed 9-iamonds, within a 6 X 9 bounding box; the optimum has a 2-row 9-cell bulk, a 2-row 5-cell middle band, with two 1-cell caps above the bulk and one 1-cell cap below the band, saving 2 cells over the row-bounded construction.
%Y A395422 Cf. A001420 (number of fixed n-iamonds), A000577 (number of free n-iamonds), A006534 (number of one-sided n-iamonds), A392363 (smallest polyiamond containing all free n-iamonds), A327094 (square-grid analog, free pieces), A000217 (triangular numbers; conjecturally coincides with the hex-grid fixed-piece container sequence for all n, proved for n = 1..7).
%K A395422 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A395422 1,1
